out of the store?

12:30.487 --> 12:31.853
- I want the truth.
- Yes.

12:31.854 --> 12:34.038
Don't... don't lie to me, Amy.

12:34.040 --> 12:36.219
- You kicked him out!
- I said yes!

12:36.220 --> 12:38.275
He was selling his book
in the store, Glenn.

12:38.277 --> 12:39.744
I didn't agree to that.

12:39.746 --> 12:42.238
You... you are out of control, missy!

12:42.239 --> 12:43.748
And... and you are going
to pick up the phone

12:43.749 --> 12:45.539
and you are gonna call Pastor Craig

12:45.540 --> 12:47.356
and apologize to him right now!

12:47.357 --> 12:48.312
No.

12:49.548 --> 12:51.481
Then you can't be manager anymore.

12:51.624 --> 12:52.923
- What?
- Yeah, I'm sorry.

12:52.925 --> 12:54.738
I thought...
I thought you could handle it,

12:54.739 --> 12:57.306
but you immediately came in and started

12:57.307 --> 12:59.785
whizzing all over the place
and changing up

12:59.786 --> 13:02.744
a perfectly good office and, "Oh, look."

13:02.745 --> 13:04.040
"Look at our window.

13:04.041 --> 13:06.137
Now we can all stare at Manager Amy."

13:06.139 --> 13:08.078
Glenn, you can't just
take the job back.

13:08.079 --> 13:09.774
Yes, I can. Get out of my office.

13:10.143 --> 13:11.642
That's not gonna happen.

13:11.644 --> 13:14.478
So... you're just keeping the job?

13:14.480 --> 13:17.539
- Yeah.
- Well then, what can I do?

13:18.522 --> 13:20.951
- Nothing.
- But then I can't do anything!

13:20.953 --> 13:22.925
- I know.
- So what? I mean,

13:22.926 --> 13:24.785
I've just gotta do whatever you say?

13:24.786 --> 13:26.829
- Yeah.
- But then I can't do what I want.

13:27.540 --> 13:29.240
And I want to do it.

13:29.589 --> 13:31.499
This is so unfair!

13:32.538 --> 13:34.404
Can I even slam the door?

13:34.667 --> 13:37.273
I'd rather that you didn't.

13:39.664 --> 13:43.033
And Jesus put forth his hand
and the leper was cured.

13:44.113 --> 13:47.136
So what miracles have you
experienced in your lives?

13:47.137 --> 13:49.304
And please, nobody say
their kids, okay?

13:49.306 --> 13:52.641
One time, I saw Lily
Tomlin in an airport.

13:52.643 --> 13:54.142
I mean, it looked like her.
I don't know.

13:54.144 --> 13:56.411
Hey, what's going on over here?

13:56.413 --> 13:59.748
Oh, nothing. Just having
a little employee Bible study.

13:59.750 --> 14:01.032
Would you care to join us?

14:01.033 --> 14:03.108
You could probably use some guidance.

14:03.109 --> 14:04.920
Ha-ha, well, can't we all?

14:04.922 --> 14:06.989
- Mm-hmm.
- But, uh, no.

14:06.991 --> 14:09.801
Unfortunately, there's no
religious gatherings allowed

14:09.802 --> 14:11.493
during company time,

14:11.495 --> 14:13.765
so everyone has to get back to work.

14:13.766 --> 14:14.792
Wow.

14:14.793 --> 14:17.966
So first Amy throws a man of
the cloth out of the store,

14:17.968 --> 14:20.068
and now we're not even allowed
to talk about the Bible.

14:20.070 --> 14:21.903
And we can't say
"Merry Christmas" anymore.

14:21.905 --> 14:23.705
Shut up, Earl. This isn't about that.

14:23.707 --> 14:26.232
Glenn, can we speak privately, please?

14:26.233 --> 14:27.743
I don't know. Can we?

14:27.745 --> 14:30.952
Okay. Glenn, I know
you're having some issues

14:30.953 --> 14:32.581
with not being in charge anymore,

14:32.583 --> 14:33.882
and so you're lashing out at me.

14:33.884 --> 14:35.817
And I'm trying to be
very cool about it,

14:35.819 --> 14:38.920
but I can't keep doing that
because it makes me look bad,

14:38.922 --> 14:42.691
so I am asking you politely.
Please knock it off.

14:42.693 --> 14:43.951
- Okay?
- Fine.

14:45.029 --> 14:47.095
But I have three minutes
left on my break.

14:47.097 --> 14:49.171
Am I allowed to talk about anything?

14:49.172 --> 14:51.099
Yes. Obviously you can talk.

14:51.101 --> 14:51.861
Fine.

14:52.436 --> 14:54.801
I'm gonna talk about, um...

14:55.606 --> 14:58.106
- John Cusack.
- Knock yourself out.

14:58.108 --> 15:00.909
Because John Cusack died for our sins,

15:00.911 --> 15:03.545
